 Many firemen have not been trained in basic first aid -- yet they are being left to care for seriously ill elderly patients for hours while they wait for an ambulance .
The Fire Brigades Union say the practice is irresponsible and dangerous but is becoming increasingly common because the ambulance service is so overstretched .
The ambulance service increasingly reliant on firemen to attend life-threatening emergencies .
South Yorkshire Fire and Rescue were sending firemen with no medical training to 999 calls .